//1. FS module.

Fs is stand for file system module from this module we can perform task related to files.fs can do a lot of things with files.
like:- 
Create
Read
Update 
Delete
Work with folders
Streams
Watch file changes

If you want to use fs module then first you need to import the fs module in your file.
Syntax for import fs module is: 
const fs=require('fs');

FS module have a lot of methods and have 3 types.
1. Synchronous Method (Blocking wait until work finish);
2. Asynchronous Method (Non-Blocking);
3. Promise-based (Modern & recommended)

1.  How to read the files with fs module in node?
(a)Asynchronous-fs.readFile()
Syntax
fs.readFile('filename','utf8',(err,data)=>{
    if(err){
        console.error(err);
        return;
    }
    console.log(data);
});

This way will not block code.

(b)Synchronous-fs.readFileSync()

const data=fs.readFileSync('filename','utf8');
console.log(data);

This way will block code.
